where Fw represents the iterative application of f w and computation of the LSTM states for d time steps. For a more detailed explanation of the formula for Fw, and a figure of the neural network architecture refer to the appendix. In this work, we consider the reduced order problem where the state of a dynamical system is projected in the reduced order space. The system is considered to be autonomous, while z ̇t = dzt/dt is the system state derivative at time step t. Following [38], the LSTM is trained using time series data from the system in the reduced order space D = {z1:T, z ̇1:T} to predict the reduced state derivative  ̇zt from a short history of the reduced order state {zt, zt−1, . . . , zt−d+1} consisting of d past temporally consecutive states. In this work, we approximated the derivative from the original time series using first-order forward differences. The loss that has to be minimized is defined as
L(D, w) = 1
