(i) Dimensionality reduction: discrete Fourier transform
Firstly, the discrete Fourier transform (DFT) is applied to the energy standardized Lorenz 96 states X ̃ j. The Fourier coefficients Xˆ k ∈ C and the inverse DFT to recover the Lorenz 96 states are given by
Xˆ k = 1
